heading: In this Order, “United Kingdom of Great Britain and Northern Ireland”
text_raw:
2. 

In this Order, “United Kingdom of Great Britain and Northern Ireland” 

includes the Channel Islands and the Isle of Man.

title: relation to the country specified in Article 3 of the following order, as to the
heading: 3. The United Kingdom of Great Britain and Northern Ireland is
text_raw:
3. The United Kingdom of Great Britain and Northern Ireland is 
designated as a safe third country for the purposes of the International 
Protection Act 2015 (No. 66 of 2015). 

GIVEN under my Official Seal, 

31 December, 2020. 

HELEN MCENTEE, 
Minister for Justice. 

Notice of the making of this Statutory Instrument was published in 
“Iris Oifigiúil” of 8th January, 2021.

text_raw:
EXPLANATORY NOTE 

(This note is not part of the Instrument and does not purport to be a legal 
interpretation.) 

This Order designates the United Kingdom of Great Britain and Northern 
Ireland as a safe third country for the purposes of the International Protection 
Act 2015.
